Still offline.
Nothing is ever simple.
Actually, on the USB-C plate that I used to plug in the battery charger, the 5V and the ground were reversed.
I swapped the wires, and now I have a charging indicator.
The ESP didn't connect right away, let's wait a few minutes.
An hour later: still offline.
It looks like it's rebooting in a loop and triggering Tasmota's reset feature.
I think the panel is just crap. I ordered a bigger one, hoping it will work.
Look at what I found in the workshop.
A 24 V panel. Unfortunately, the sun is so low (and partly hidden by a tree) that it drops to almost nothing as soon as I use it.
I think I'll wait until tomorrow to see if it's enough for this installation or if I need the best panel I ordered.
According to Amazon, I bought the panel in 2021, and it should generate up to 12 V at a maximum of 1.2 A.
Either something is wrong with this panel or with my multimeter, or they have changed the specs.
Good news everyone!
They changed the specifications and the one I have is H.S.
The titles of the old and new specifications mention a 12 V, 10 W panel.
That's why I don't delete my old emails.
Hey, look: the thing has reconnected for about a half minute about an hour ago.
Maybe the panel charged the battery just enough for 38 seconds of power. It would only have taken a bit more than two hours.
Guess what: it's cloudy today. So I'm not sure if this solar panel (probably broken) can generate enough energy to do anything.
